"async\" src=\"https:\/\/manninglaw.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/MLF-Taylor-Manning-c.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"320\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-1460 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/manninglaw.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/MLF-Taylor-Manning-c.jpg 256w, https:\/\/manninglaw.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/MLF-Taylor-Manning-c-240x300.jpg 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 256px) 100vw, 256px\" \/><a href=\"https:\/\/www.manninglaw.com\/criminal-attorneys-raleigh\/t-taylor-manning\/\"><strong>Taylor Manning<\/strong><\/a> joined his father at Manning Law Firm following three years of practice with a general practice law firm in eastern North Carolina. Taylor Manning has spent the last several years here in Raleigh growing his expertise in all types of criminal law matters. On any given day, you will find him in both the District and Superior Courts of Wake and surrounding counties advocating for and representing both privately retained and judicially appointed clients.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div style=\"height:10px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"alignleft size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"256\" height=\"320\" src=\"https:\/\/manninglaw.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/MLF-Clarke-Martin-headshot-c.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1456\" style=\"width:256px;height:320px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/manninglaw.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/MLF-Clarke-Martin-headshot-c.jpg 256w, https:\/\/manninglaw.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/MLF-Clarke-Martin-headshot-c-240x300.jpg 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 256px) 100vw, 256px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/manninglaw.com\/criminal-attorneys-raleigh\/clarke-s-martin\">Clarke S. Martin<\/a><\/strong> joined the firm as an associate in September 2022, following two years of service as judicial law clerk at the United States District Court for the Middle District of North Carolina.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a third-year law student, Clarke sat second chair in a first-degree murder trial in Wake County, under the supervision of the lead attorney. The jury returned a verdict of not guilty as to the charge of murder. Clarke worked for the firm as a summer law clerk while in law school, and also volunteered as a student advocate for the Juvenile Parole Project in the Pro Bono Program at Carolina Law where she successfully argued in favor of a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ncdps.gov\/adult-corrections\/prisons\/transition-services\/mutual-agreement-parole\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MAPP Contract<\/a> for a client who was originally sentenced to life in prison for crimes they committed as a juvenile.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>She speaks fluent French and beginner-level Welsh.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Contact Manning Law Firm, PLLC.<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure you leave your case in the hands of an attorney you trust. If you would like to learn more about our attorneys or schedule a meeting, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.manninglaw.com\/contact\/\">contact us today<\/a> to get started. We are happy to stand by your side with the experience and dedication you deserve.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Meet Our Attorneys Hiring the right attorney to tackle your case takes careful planning and consideration on your part. You want to hire someone you trust to successfully defend you when you need it the most. The attorneys at Manning Law Firm have the expertise and dedication you need on your side. Learn more about&#8230; <a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/manninglaw.com\/criminal-attorneys-raleigh\/\" title=\"ReadOur Attorneys\">Read more &raquo;<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","template":"","meta":{"_acf_cha